# Neglectedness

While there seem to be various books (especially pop science and self-help books)
written on the subject of romance, as well as various online communities dedicated
to helping people meet their romantic needs (e.g. the pick-up artistry movement),
romance doesn't seem to be thought of as a cause to focus on, in the sense that e.g.
life extension or existential risk or climate change are thought of as causes.
Approaches to solving this problem seem rather disparate at the moment, where e.g.
each author of a book advocates their own preferred approach (which may or may not
work for others). In other words, there seems to be a lack of concerted effort
at seriously trying to solve this problem.

More recently, there have been various attempts to solve the matching problem in
romance through online dating sites (e.g. OkCupid) and various apps (most notorious
perhaps is Tinder). However it's unclear how successful these have been.


